---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Terms of Service — Social Text Toolkit" description="Terms of Service for Social Text Toolkit. Free tools for text decoration. Use at your own discretion. No warranties, no liability for how you use generated content.">
  <article class="prose prose-lg dark:prose-invert max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-6">Terms of Service</h1>
    <p class="text-sm text-[var(--text-secondary)] mb-8"><em>Last updated: June 17, 2026</em></p>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)] mt-8 mb-4">1. Acceptance of Terms</h2>
    <p class="text-[var(--text-secondary)] leading-relaxed mb-4">
      By accessing or using Social Text Toolkit ("the Service"), you agree to be bound by these Terms of Service. If you do not agree, please do not use the Service.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)] mt-8 mb-4">2. Description of Service</h2>
    <p class="text-[var(--text-secondary)] leading-relaxed mb-4">
      Social Text Toolkit provides free, browser-based tools for generating decorated Unicode text, browsing symbols, creating text art, and previewing social media bio content. All tools operate entirely within your web browser and do not require account registration.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)] mt-8 mb-4">3. Acceptable Use</h2>
    <p class="text-[var(--text-secondary)] leading-relaxed mb-4">You agree to use the Service only for lawful purposes. You may not:</p>
    <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-[var(--text-secondary)] space-y-2 mb-4">
      <li>Use the generated text or symbols for spam, harassment, impersonation, or any illegal activity.</li>
      <li>Attempt to disrupt, overload, or compromise the Service through automated means, scraping, or denial-of-service attacks.</li>
      <li>Use the Service to distribute malware, phishing links, or harmful code.</li>
      <li>Violate the terms of service of any third-party platform (Instagram, TikTok, Discord, etc.) where you may use the generated content.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)] mt-8 mb-4">4. Intellectual Property</h2>
    <p class="text-[var(--text-secondary)] leading-relaxed mb-4">
      The tools, website design, code, and original content of Social Text Toolkit are protected by copyright and are made available under an open-source license. Unicode characters, symbols, and kaomoji are not subject to copyright as they are part of the Unicode standard or are common cultural expressions.
    </p>
    <p class="text-[var(--text-secondary)] leading-relaxed mb-4">
      You are free to use any text or symbols generated by our tools for personal or commercial purposes. We claim no ownership over the output of our tools.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)] mt-8 mb-4">5. No Warranty</h2>
    <p class="text-[var(--text-secondary)] leading-relaxed mb-4">
      The Service is provided "as is" and "as available" without any warranties, express or implied. We do not guarantee that:
    </p>
    <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-[var(--text-secondary)] space-y-2 mb-4">
      <li>The Service will be uninterrupted, secure, or error-free.</li>
      <li>Generated text or symbols will display correctly on all platforms and devices.</li>
      <li>Platform compatibility labels are 100% accurate (platforms may change their Unicode support at any time).</li>
      <li>Text generated by our tools will not be filtered or blocked by third-party platforms.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)] mt-8 mb-4">6. Limitation of Liability</h2>
    <p class="text-[var(--text-secondary)] leading-relaxed mb-4">
      To the fullest extent permitted by law, Social Text Toolkit and its creators shall not be liable for any direct, indirect, incidental, consequential, or special damages arising from your use of or inability to use the Service. This includes, but is not limited to, damages from platform account restrictions due to use of generated content, loss of data stored in your browser's localStorage, or any other losses.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)] mt-8 mb-4">7. Platform Compatibility Disclaimer</h2>
    <p class="text-[var(--text-secondary)] leading-relaxed mb-4">
      Our platform compatibility labels (Instagram, TikTok, Discord, Twitter/X, etc.) reflect testing at the time of publication. Social media platforms may update their Unicode support at any time, which may cause previously compatible characters to display as boxes or be filtered. We recommend testing important content before publishing.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)] mt-8 mb-4">8. Changes to Terms</h2>
    <p class="text-[var(--text-secondary)] leading-relaxed mb-4">
      We reserve the right to modify these Terms of Service at any time. Changes will be effective immediately upon posting. Your continued use of the Service after changes constitutes acceptance of the updated terms.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)] mt-8 mb-4">9. Contact</h2>
    <p class="text-[var(--text-secondary)] leading-relaxed mb-4">
      For questions about these Terms, please visit our <a href="/contact" class="text-brand-500 hover:text-brand-600 underline">Contact page</a>.
    </p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
